HIV/SIN: Kasar Sin ta samu karin mutane 14 cikin 100 da suka kamu da cutar
Kasar Sin ta samu karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da kuma cutar kanjamau.
A cewar ma'aikatar lafiya, mutane fiye da 820,000 ne suka kamu da cutar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai, an samu sabbin mutane kusan 40 000.
Yawancin sabbin cututtukan da aka samu sun samo asali ne daga jima'i, wanda ya nuna canji daga baya.
A al'adance, cutar HIV tana yaduwa cikin sauri a wasu sassan kasar Sin ta hanyar shan jini da ke dauke da cutar.
Amma, adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar ta hanyar wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji ma'aikatar lafiya ta ƙasar Sin a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Duk da haka, kowace shekara, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da kuma ciwon baya a China yana ƙaruwa da 100,000.
Yaduwar cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT a China.
A shekarar 1997 aka haramta luwadi a kasar Sin, amma nuna bambanci ga mutane a cikin al'ummomin KGB ya zama ruwan dare gama gari.
Bincike ya nuna cewa saboda tsattsauran ra'ayi, kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin dari na maza da suka yi jima'i da maza sukan auri mata.
Yawancin cututtukan cututtuka suna faruwa ne saboda rashin kariya a cikin waɗannan dangantaka.
A shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin HIV ga kowa a kasar a matsayin wani bangare na kokarin magance cutar.
